-- Jumeirah to Manage Sberbank’s Hotel Near Kremlin, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-30T04:23:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-30/jumeirah-to-manage-sberbank-s-hotel-near-kremlin-vedomosti-says.html
Jumeirah Group, which manages the
Burj Al Arab hotel in Dubai, won the contract to manage the
Tsarev Sad apartment hotel near the Moscow Kremlin,  Vedomosti 
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the matter.  Sberbank Capital, a unit of Sberbank,  Russia ’s largest
lender, and its partner Midland Development, plan to invest
about $300 million to build 72,000 square meters of apartments
and offices at Tsarev Sad, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  